It seems that the issue persists. 

Let me try a different approach. Here is an example of how you can create an XML file in a text editor and then save it with a `.xml` extension:
```
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<missionPlan xmlns:m="http://robotictaskrepresentation.org/schemas/missionplan.xsd"
             xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
             xsi:schemaLocation="http://robotictaskrepresentation.org/schemas/missionplan.xsd 
                                 http://robotictaskrepresentation.org/schemas/missionplan.xsd">
  <CompositeTaskInformation>
    <tasks>
      <m:TaskDescription xml:lang="en">Drive to tree with id 0</m:TaskDescription>
      <m:DrivingToTree>
        <treeId>0</treeId>
      </m:DrivingToTree>
      <m:ActionType>
        <actionTypeCode>DetermineTemperature</actionTypeCode>
        <description>Take a picture of the temperature reading</description>
      </m:ActionType>
    </tasks>

    <m:TaskDescription xml:lang="en">Analyze picture to determine if temperature is low</m:TaskDescription>
    <CompositeTaskInformation>
      <tasks>
        <m:TaskDescription xml:lang="en">Drive to tree with id 0</m:TaskDescription>
        <m:DrivingToTree>
          <treeId>0</treeId>
        </m:DrivingToTree>
        <m:ActionType>
          <actionTypeCode>DetermineTemperature</actionTypeCode>
          <description>Analyze picture to determine if temperature is low</description>
        </m:ActionType>
      </tasks>

      <!-- Conditional outcome -->
      <ConditionalOutcome>
        <outcomeTypeCode>LowTemperature</outcomeTypeCode>
        <nextTask>
          <m:TaskDescription xml:lang="en">Take a co2 sample</m:TaskDescription>
          <CompositeTaskInformation>
            <tasks>
              <m:TaskDescription xml:lang="en">Drive to tree with id 0</m:TaskDescription>
              <m:DrivingToTree>
                <treeId>0</treeId>
              </m:DrivingToTree>
              <m:ActionType>
                <actionTypeCode>DetermineCO2</actionTypeCode>
                <description>Take a co2 sample</description>
              </m:ActionType>
            </tasks>
          </CompositeTaskInformation>
        </nextTask>
      </ConditionalOutcome>

      <!-- Outcome -->
      <Outcome>
        <outcomeTypeCode>HighTemperature</outcomeTypeCode>
        <distanceTraveled>0 km</distanceTraveled>
      </Outcome>
    </CompositeTaskInformation>

    <!-- Repeat process -->
    <m:TaskDescription xml:lang="en">Drive to far away tree and repeat</m:TaskDescription>
    <m:DrivingToTree>
      <treeId>farAwayTree</treeId>
    </m:DrivingToTree>
    <m:ActionType>
      <actionTypeCode>DetermineTemperature</actionTypeCode>
      <description>Analyze picture to determine if temperature is low</description>
    </m:ActionType>

    <!-- Continue repeating until low temperature reading -->
    <ConditionalOutcome>
      <outcomeTypeCode>LowTemperature</outcomeTypeCode>
      <nextTask>
        <!-- Repeat process -->
      </nextTask>
    </ConditionalOutcome>

    <m:Outcome>
      <outcomeTypeCode>EndMission</outcomeTypeCode>
      <distanceTraveled>10 km</distanceTraveled>
    </m:Outcome>
  </CompositeTaskInformation>
</missionPlan>
```
Please copy and paste this into a text editor, then save it as an XML file. Try opening the file in an XML viewer or editor to see if you can view its contents correctly.

Alternatively, you can use a tool like Notepad++ on Windows or TextMate on Mac to create and edit XML files. These tools often have built-in XML validation features that can help you identify and fix errors in your XML code.